The probability that at least two people in a room of 30 do not share a birthday is the complement of the probability that all 30 people share the same birthday. This is calculated as:

\[
1 - \left(\frac{1}{365}\right)^{29}
\]

This value is extremely close to 1, as the chance of all 30 people sharing the same birthday is astronomically low.

**Answer:** \boxed{1 - \left(\frac{1}{365}\right)^{29}}
